'''Bellingshausen Plain''' ({{coord|64|0|S|90|0|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}), also known as '''Bellinghausen Abyssal Plain''', is an undersea plain parallel to the continental rise in the [[Bellingshausen Sea]], named for Admiral [[Fabian Gottlieb von Bellingshausen]], commander of the [[Russian Antarctic Expedition]] (1818–1821). The name was approved by the [[Advisory Committee for Undersea Features]] in April, 1974.

