'''Dobrun Monastery''' ({{lang-sr-cyr|Манастир Добрун}}) is located in [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], 12 km away from town of [[Višegrad]], in the gorge of the [[Rzav (Drina)|Rzav river]] near the border with [[Republic of Serbia]]. Dobrun Monastery is dedicated to the [[Dormition of the Virgin]] and was built in 1343 by Duke [[Pribil]] and his sons Stefan and Petar.

