This article lists the '''colonial governors of [[Cameroon]]'''. It encompasses the period when the country was under colonial rule of the [[German Empire]] (as [[Kamerun]]), occupation of the territory by the [[Allies of World War I|Allies]] during [[World War I]] ([[Kamerun Campaign]]), as well as the period when it was under the administration of [[France]] (as [[French Cameroons]]) and the [[United Kingdom]] (as [[British Cameroons]]) respectively.
