'''Slingerland''' is a [[Dutch language|Dutch]] [[toponymic surname]]. It refers to an origin in the [[heerlijkheid]] of Slingelandt, now covered by the former community of [[Nederslingeland]] and the town of [[Overslingeland]] in [[South Holland]]. Variants are ''(Van) Slingeland'' and ''Slingelandt''. <ref>[http://www.cbgfamilienamen.nl/nfb/detail_naam.php?gba_lcnaam=slingerland&gba_naam=Slingerland&nfd_naam=Slingerland&operator=eq&taal= Slingerland] at the Database of Surnames in The Netherlands</ref> Many Americans named Slingerland are descendants of Dutch settler Teunis Cornelis Slingerland (1617, [[Amsterdam]] – 1700, [[Hackensack, New Jersey]]).<ref>Paul Grondahl, [https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Digging-into-Slingerland-family-history-5655541.php Digging into Slingerland family history], Times Union, July 30, 2014</ref> Notable people with the name include:
* [[Cashandra Slingerland]] (born 1974), South African road cyclist * [[H.H. Slingerland]] (1875–1946), American founder of the Slingerland Drum Company * {{illm|James S. Slingerland|de|}} (1834–1874), American politician, vice governor of Nevada from 1867 to 1871 * [[Jared Slingerland]] (born 1984), Canadian guitarist and electronic musician * [[John I. Slingerland]] (1804–1861), United States Representative from New York ;Van Slingeland(t): *[[Cornelis van Slingeland]] (1635–1686), Dutch portrait painter *[[Pieter Cornelisz van Slingelandt]] (1640–1691), Dutch portrait painter *[[Simon van Slingelandt]] (1664–1736), Grand Pensionary of Holland from 1727 to 1736
==See also== * [[Slingerland Drum Company]] * [[Slingerlands, New York]], a hamlet named for the post master William H. Slingerland
