'''Talish-i Gushtasbi''' ([[persian language|Persian]]: تالش گشتاسبی) is the historical name of the northern [[Talysh people|Talysh]] area, presently a part of the [[Republic of Azerbaijan]]. During the Abbasid Caliphate, there was a (partially equivalent) region called Gushtasfi ([[persian language|Persian]]: گشتاسفی). People of northern Talysh are of [[Iran]]ian stock and speak a northwestern [[Iranian language]] called [[Talysh language|Talysh]]. The chief cities of the area are [[Talesh, Iran|Talesh]], [[Lankaran]], [[Lerik, Azerbaijan|Lerik]], [[Masally]] and [[Astara, Azerbaijan|Astara]].

